  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nI am trying to run the tests automatically so I can do TDD with an easy, fun worklfow.\r\n\r\nHowever, the watch mode doesn't seem to be working properly (not running tests) when I do this command:\r\n```\r\ntruffle watch\r\n```\r\n\r\nor\r\n\r\n```\r\ntruffle watch --tests\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlso, it's making me nervous and sad that the docs are saying the watch command in deprecated. üò¢\r\n\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2021-05-31 at 11 32 56 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5354163/120262849-89d8b480-c268-11eb-82e9-383a39338727.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso, it's odd to me that there is no recommendation for the \"new way\" to run tests in watch mode with this now deprecated. It's kind of just like, \"welp, sorry but you're beat!\" üòÖ\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nHonestly though, I think watch mode as a flag for \"truffle test\" would be the most natural and intuitive way to have it.\r\n\r\nConsider other javascript test runners like jest or mocha:\r\n\r\n```\r\njest --watch\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nmocha --watch\r\n```\r\n\r\nwith `-w` alis:\r\n```\r\nmocha -w\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be great if truffle test (and possibly other truffle commands) supported things syntax:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntruffle test --watch\r\n```\r\n\r\nor with the alias:\r\n```\r\ntruffle test -w\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks! ‚ô•Ô∏è\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
