    "body": "Here's a nice way of doing it that I've been using:\r\n\r\n(make you have a package.json file first: `npm init`)\r\n\r\nThen install nodemon as a dev dependency:\r\n```\r\nnpm i -D nodemon\r\n```\r\n\r\nUse these scripts in your package.json for running tests and allowing it to watch solidity and javascript files, running \"truffle test\" when there are any changes:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"scripts\": {\r\n    \"test\": \"truffle test\",\r\n    \"test:watch\": \"nodemon --ext 'js,sol' --exec 'truffle test'\"\r\n  },\r\n```",
